This project originated in the context of a Swiss Data Science Center ([SDSC](https://datascience.ch/)) Collaborative project "BioDetect", c19-10. 

The collaboration was between the Swiss Federal Office for Forest, Snow and Landscape Research ([WSL](https://www.wsl.ch/en.html)), The Swiss Federal Institute of Acquatic Science and Technology ([EAWAG](https://www.eawag.ch/en/)), and the [SDSC](https://datascience.ch/). 

Authors of the dataset and software: 

- Luca Pegoraro (WSL): co-authored all scripts, wrote all documentation and curated deployment. 
- Michele Volpi (SDSC): authored the main functionality of the package, and trained the ML models. 
- Danina Schmidt (EAWAG): acquired the image data, studied the camera setups and acquisition process, made all the taxonomic and lengths annotations. 
- Nico Baetz, Christine Weber (EAWAG): contributed MZB samples, provided feedback. 
- Catherine Graham (WSL): acquired funding and provided feedback throughout the project. 
- Blake Matthews (EAWAG): acquired funding and provided feedback throughout the project. 